coconut
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Pacific Islander (orig. prob. applied by Maori to other Polynesians, esp. in Auckland).
Origin:[none]
Register: offensive

Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. Raro
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1955 heard used by an Auckland Maori. 1984 17 M E105Pakuranga Coll. 24E  COCONUTS
