Edition:
Quote: In addition to referring to the usual hairy milk filled nut, this appellation is used as a derisive name for Pacific Islanders living in New Zealand. The term is most often used by Maoris who resent the Islanders' attempts to move in to the jobs and neighborhoods that are their customary reserve.
